-- Cayman Islands Golf Course Seeking Water Plant, CayCompass Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-10-24T18:55:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-24/cayman-islands-golf-course-seeking-water-plant-caycompass-says.html
A golf club in the  Cayman Islands  is
seeking approval for an on-site reverse osmosis plant to produce
fresh water from the Caribbean for its golf course,
CayCompass.com reported, citing planning authorities.  The North Sound Golf Club project, estimated to cost at
least $1.5 million for the plant, tank and fencing, has received
planning permission and now must be granted a concession from
island authorities, according to CayCompass.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
